# Nadezhdino, Aurgazinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Nadezhdino () is a rural locality (a village) in Urshaksky Selsoviet, Aurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 42 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Nadezhdino is located 40 km northwest of Tolbazy (the district's administrative centre) by road. Subkhangulovo is the nearest rural locality.
